pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132001908,imgsize-74568.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ethiopian proverb of the day: 'When spider webs unite, they can tie up a lion']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132000451.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The ancient Ethiopian saying, "When spider webs unite, they can tie up a lion," is a compelling reminder that working together is vital for overcoming great obstacles. This proverb highlights the strength found in unity and collaboration, illustrating how collective effort can yield remarkable results, even in the face of adversity. It calls for a recognition of our interconnectedness, inspiring communities to join forces for a common cause.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/ethiopian-proverb-of-the-day-when-spider-webs-unite-they-can-tie-up-a-lion-how-collective-action-can-defeat-great-power/articleshow/132000451.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/ethiopian-proverb-of-the-day-when-spider-webs-unite-they-can-tie-up-a-lion-how-collective-action-can-defeat-great-power/articleshow/132000451.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-25T23:36:21+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132000859,imgsize-130876.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[German proverb of the day: 'The stupidest farmers have the biggest potatoes']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131999432.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A German proverb states, 'The stupidest farmers have the biggest potatoes,' shedding light on the unexpected nature of success. This saying emphasizes that luck and other external factors often play a crucial role in determining outcomes—particularly in unpredictable areas like agriculture. Its relevance extends beyond farming to business and social media, serving as a reminder that visible achievements do not always equate to genuine skill or ability.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/german-proverb-of-the-day-the-stupidest-farmers-have-the-biggest-potatoes-a-witty-reminder-that-success-doesnt-always-go-to-the-smartest-people/articleshow/131999432.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/german-proverb-of-the-day-the-stupidest-farmers-have-the-biggest-potatoes-a-witty-reminder-that-success-doesnt-always-go-to-the-smartest-people/articleshow/131999432.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-25T23:12:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131999534,imgsize-132674.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Non-citizens arriving at US border do not automatically get asylum, can be turned away]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131998673.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/non-citizens-arriving-at-us-border-do-not-automatically-get-asylum-can-be-turned-away-supreme-court-backs-trump-administration/articleshow/131998673.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/non-citizens-arriving-at-us-border-do-not-automatically-get-asylum-can-be-turned-away-supreme-court-backs-trump-administration/articleshow/131998673.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-25T22:37:47+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclos